text: Hi <@U0548MM6B>, the Android scene is fairly mature.  Lots of small companies between Toronto and Waterloo, plus many of the large Web companies have offices here, e.g. Google, Facebook, etc...
I wouldn't say companies mostly hire direct from colleges; my opening is a good example, where we are hiring a senior dev with plenty of experience

file.title: Android Engineer @ Highwinds
file.preview:
JOB SUMMARY:  

We are looking for an experienced and talented Android Engineer to join our growing Client Application Development team, or “App Dev.” As one of the Android Engineers, you will be working with the rest of the App Dev team to provide a great client experience across a wide range of applications and platforms. We work in a fun, fast-paced, agile environment with a team excited about adding new members to accomplish more features. All our applications are 100% native, and use the latest design guidelines.

text: Hit me up if you are interested in joining <@U055GGAHS> and me at Highwinds. Plenty of cool stuff like: We celebrate pretty much any national food day, some recents like Pizza, Sushi, Cereal, and Grilled Cheese with catered food from local restaurants and food trucks. Tickets to NBA basketball games, and usually a good movie every other month where we rent the theater out and go as a company early in the afternoon. Free Healthcare and that jazz, plus we sponsor attending cool events like I/O (sending someone for WWDC for example)
